						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the central shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅgachōḷa III. Year 15: 1192-93 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This records the gift of a perpetual lamp by Periyāṇḍāḷ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Aṉṉadāṉa Naṅgai, wife of Appaṉ Kaḻaṉi, of Śiṟuvāymukam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kulōttuṅgaśōḻapaṭṭiṉam and Śilaiśeṭṭi Kāri Āḻvāṉ also of Śiṟuvāymukam to the god Tirumaṟaikkāḍu Uḍaiyār in Kuṉṟūr-nāḍu, a sub-division of Umbaḷa-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
